      Makeupedia allows you to subsitute words with another word or phrase on a Wikipedia page.  An account is not mandatory but you can save your humorous changes if you log in.
      <br><br>
      <h3>Wow, this is cool.  How do I start using this site?</h3>
      <ol>
      <li>Easy! Type in your search term in the field and hit the submit button.</li>
      <li>Next, the Wikipedia page will load.  Here, you can select the text you want to change.</li>
      <li>A new window will appear. The text you selected in step 2 will be in the top field. You can still edit the field by selecting or typing words into it.  Enter the word or phrase you want to replace the selected text with in the bottom, "Replace with" field.  Hit the submit button, that's it! (Note: at this time, you can't expect a replacement to occur on text that is a mixture of links and non-links)</li>
      <li>The page will load again with your changes!  Repeat steps 2-3 again to make multiple changes.</li>
      </ol>
